title: unauthenticated attacker
extract: An authenticated attack requires an attacker to know information about the target to pull off an exploit of the vulnerability. ... On the other hand, an unauthenticated attack requires no knowledge about a target system. An example of this is a worm that exploits an operating system service without needed any information.Sep 21, 2012
